First time I visited this place, and it is an instant favorite. The name of this place holds true. The food was very fresh. The variety of options is a bit overwhelming at first, but they have a good menu to get you started. I ordered the brown rice bowl, customized it to my liking, and had it stir fried. Wow. The food was delicious!  The cilantro vinagrette, sliced parm, and red sauce on top of the food was an amazing combo that really gave the dish a great flavor. They have so many healthy foods to choose from. My wife got a greek salad and really enjoyed it, too. My daughter loved the mac and cheese from the kids menu. I also liked that they had a full nutritional breakdown of all their menu items that you could access online. I guess to sum it up, the food is healthy, it's fresh, it's delicious, and I wish they would open one up in Frederick, Md!

She threw my salad together carelessly and put in cheese as I told her not to. When she put my salad in my bowl, she threw it in so carelessly that some of it spilled on to the table and never made it into my bowl. This restaurant uses way too much plastic, too - they should convert to using paper bowls for take out and biodegradable utensils and ditch the plastic bag.

They serve a variety of meal salads and also “bowls”. (Check out their menu for better detail). I had the Asian bowl with salmon as my protein. I also had turkey chili. My items were a little more peppery than bowls or turkey chili I have had elsewhere; I like it this way, but I know some people would find it too hot. I don’t know if this is typical there everyday. This place is a breath of fresh air from the standard fat-laden foods in the touristy chain restaurants of the area. I like a crab cake once in a while, but sometimes you need a break from steak and seafood.

I wish I could give them anything below 1 star. I have been vegetarian all my life and I ordered a salad without any meat but tofu that was chopped small and marinated with herbs.  Being busy I eat at my desk with very little time to pay attention to my meal. 2nd or 3rd bite felt different and I noticed it wasn't tofu. It was chicken that looked like tofu. Went back to the store and the manger was super indifferent about whole matter. I was like I am so upset that I ate something I have avoided all my life by choice. On other thought what if there was something in that salad that I was allergic to? But the manager could care less. I will never go back!!!
